stimulusHtml: Which of the following best describes the preconditions necessary for the method to run without error?

features.html:
Consider the following method.

 

public static void processNumbers(ArrayList<Integer> numbers)
{
   int last = numbers.size() - 1;
   numbers.add(0, numbers.get(last));
   numbers.remove(last + 1);
}

choicesHtml: The  ArrayList  must be sorted from smallest to largest.
The  ArrayList  must contain at least one element.
The  ArrayList  must contain at least two elements.
The  ArrayList  must contain only positive  Integer  values.
